author: Alison Sider
title: Crude Prices Higher as Saudi Prince Visits U.S.
text:
Oil prices climbed more than 2% to three-week highs Tuesday as Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salmanâ€™s visit to Washington raised the prospect of a more aggressive stance toward Iran.
U.S. crude futures rose $1.34, or 2.16%, to $63.40 a barrel on the New York Mercantile Exchange. Brent, the global benchmark, rose $1.37, or 2.07%, to $67.42 a barrel on ICE Futures Europe. Both benchmarks settled at their highest level since Feb. 26.
